The paper discusses index structures in data management systems, which is a topic that falls under the database (cs.DB) sub-category. The use of deep learning models to replace traditional index structures suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the theoretical analysis of learned indexes, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of learned indexes on real-world data sets, which suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
